[2] Spain (Valencia)
Date: Wed 5 Jun 2019 19:02 CEST
Source: La Vanguardia, Agencia EFE report [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.lavanguardia.com/local/valencia/20190605/462700160795/sanidad-detecta-un-brote-de-tosferina-en-requena-con-7-casos-confirmados.html


The Conselleria de Sanitat [Ministry of Health of the Generalitat Valenciana] has detected an outbreak of whooping cough in the town of Requena, which has affected 7 people aged between 10 and 44 years.

According to sources from the Conselleria, the outbreak was declared on [27 May 2019] and to date there are 7 confirmed cases, although none have required hospitalization and all are evolving without complications.

The proceedings were initiated that same day, with the application of the protocol for pertussis surveillance and outbreak control, which includes recommendations for treatment and isolation of cases, and identification of contacts to review their vaccination status and administer prophylaxis antibiotic if applicable.

That same day, this information was also communicated to the school management so that they could send the parents an informative circular about whooping cough and its prevention, so that they could check the children's immunization status and contact their doctor or pediatrician in case of being high-risk contact.

