[6] Argentina (Cordoba)
Date: Tue 11 Jun 2019
Source: Filo News [in Spanish, machine trans., abbreviated, edited]
https://www.filo.news/actualidad/Se-triplicaron-en-Cordoba-los-casos-de-tos-ferina-o-tos-convulsa-20190611-0013.html


The [Cordoba] Provincial Health Ministry has verified a total of 56 cases of whooping cough in 2019, caused by the bacterium _Bordetella pertussis_, against the 19 registered in the same period last year [2018].

64% of the cases correspond to children younger than 6 months whose mothers had not been vaccinated.

This year [2019], the outbreak of respiratory diseases came earlier, with more serious illnesses. And it not only has to do with the lack of vaccination but also with a specific issue of the germ that is mutating and there tend to be increased cases every 4 years.

--
